==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saprophyte
<hw>Sap"ro*phyte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>sapro`s</grk> rotten + <grk>fyto`n</grk> a plant.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any plant growing on decayed animal or vegetable
matter, as most fungi and some flowering plants with no green color, as
the Indian pipe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saprophytic</ent>⟦br⟧
